caption: So delicious & wonderful service! Great outdoor area too. They have my favorite kind of falafel (green, cause when you know - you know). I highly recommend asking about their sesame bread. A great find in Brooklyn!

Definitely the worst middle-Eastern food I’ve ever had. We ordered a selection of their platters (chicken, lamb and falafel) and it was across the board DRY, TASTELESS and WILTED. Just plain bad. Did I mention it was dry? Dry to the point of being inedible. One star because they were friendly. But that doesn’t matter when the food is so atrocious. AVOID!

Food is so good here. Good prices too! Really recommend the falafel sandwich, anything lamb, and the Avocado smoothie. This place is more of a takeaway place, because it’s small and only has a couple of tables. The service could be improved— sometimes the food takes a while, sometimes it’s really quick, it seems like it just depends on who’s taking your order. They’re always friendly, but just seem disorganized. I’ve ordered takeout a couple of times, and I’ve gotten odd service to say the least. One time, I ordered a sandwich to pickup, and the person on the phone hung up without asking my name or giving me an ETA. The call lasted about 20 seconds. Also, please improve the way takeout fries are packaged! They came piping hot in a greasy paper bag that was already starting to fall apart by the time I got it. For the record I live a few blocks away so delivery takes probably 2-3 min. Aluminum foil-wrapped, maybe? I do really like this place and I want to see them do well in these hard times! Highly recommend giving this place a visit.

This has been one of my fav Brooklyn spots for years now. One of those places that do not lose on quality with time. Affordable prices, kind staff, delicious Yemeni tea, and hands down to the best sandwiches in Brooklyn (highly recommend the skirt steak sandwich 😋).
I don’t appreciate their service over phone calls they are rude, they don’t pick up and delivery is always late!!

It has a completely different vibe from every other business on the block because of the green and welcoming decor - flowers on every table. The food is Middle Eastern mixed with American and I ordered their bestseller because of that. A little greasy but so yummy and you know the grease is coming from the fries they just put into the Kifta Wrap. Also got to enjoy a cuppa Lebanese Tea, strong but not too sweet - would also highly recommend.

Stopped by tonight for a quick dinner, first visit ever.  We ordered a lamb shawarma sandwich, catfish sandwich and a falafel hummus platter.  The place is tiny, don't expect to sit, but good service.  The lamb shawarma was delicious. They knocked it out of the park with tender lamb and a great flavour. The falafel was mediocre, chewy and a little dry.  The catfish sandwich sounded like a great idea but was disappointing.  Great baklava and mint tea were a nice cherry on top of the meal.
